<TITLE> BFF prepares disciplinary code </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 28 (bdnews24.com)  The Bangladesh Football Federation is preparing a common disciplinary code for its approved clubs, associations, organisations, players, officials and all persons related to the country's most popular game. "We are preparing a disciplinary code titled "BFF Disciplinary Code" for its approved clubs, players, officials and all persons related to football in the light of the FIFA Standard Disciplinary Code," said B. League manager Abu Nayeem Shohag, who is also involved in formulating the code. He said that the BFF would take disciplinary action in future on the basis of the BFF disciplinary code once it is approved by the BFF executive committee and the FIFA, the world's highest football governing body. Shohag said that the five-member BFF disciplinary committee, headed by Mezbahuddin Ahmed, would finalise the draft in its next meeting and would send it to the BFF executive committee for the final approval. He said that the draft code would consist of 138 articles such as sanctions applicable to legal persons and natural persons, ban on playing in a particular stadium, playing a match on a neutral ground, demotion to the lower division, deduction of points, suspension, return of awards, reprimand, warning, fine, caution, expulsion, match suspension, ban on dressing room or substitute's bench, ban on taking part in football- related activities, stadium ban, playing a match without spectators. The code also includes infringement of laws of the game, offensive and racist behaviour, intimidation, corruption and doping etc. The BFF manager also said that clubs, players, persons and associations would be able to appeal against the verdict of the disciplinary committee if they thought they were deprived of justice. 
